name: a fickle light #6
description:
"Temporal disorientation covers both alterations in circadian clocks and photoperiodism as well as the partitioning of activity between day and night."
Insects internal clocks are often governed by moon or day length cues. Artificial light can desynchronise duration of feeding, mating and egg-laying.
From a series - a fickle light - that focuses on artificial light and its effect on urban fauna and flora.
